                   "message":  "MENU-ENABLEMENT-DOC-RECONCILE: record #313/#314 (dynamic menu enablement shipped), docs-only\n\nForward-only state-doc reconcile. Registry-driven dynamic menu enablement landed\n(#313 MENU-ENABLED-SUBSTRATE 459c689 + #314 MENU-DYNAMIC-RESOLVE 10790ba), but the\nlive state docs still listed \"the W08 registry-driven dynamic predicates +\nper-frame re-resolve\" as DEFERRED and framed the bespoke MenuStateHandoff /\nplay_item_enabled Play-greying as the live mechanism.\n\nRecords that #313/#314 shipped it: the menu re-resolves PER FRAME against a live\nPredicateContext and greys items via the canonical registry path (ResolvedEntry.\nenabled -\u003e add_enabled); the keyboard routes via enabled_command_for_shortcut; the\nbespoke MenuStateHandoff / MenuStateSnapshot (deleted) / play_item_enabled channel\nis retired -- ONE canonical enablement path. Rough-edge fix: File Save/Open/Save-As\ngrey out outside Editing (were always-enabled -\u003e looked clickable but no-op\u0027d\nduring Play).\n\nSupersedes the W08-ACCELERATOR (#312) snapshot\u0027s \"dynamic predicates + per-frame\nre-resolve ... deferred (menu resolves once with PredicateContext::default();\nstatic index)\" line and the PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC (#302) bespoke-greying framing.\n\nDeferred list narrowed CAREFULLY (NOT claimed done): Play/View accelerator\ndisplay+execution; AcceleratorTable conflict UI/population; dynamic toggle labels\n(Play\u003c-\u003ePause, camera-state View); plugin menu entries; host-\u003eshell FIFO\nmenu-click replacement (only the keyboard\u0027s enablement was unified, not the click\ntransport); generalized command execution beyond the canonical entries; the\nvisibility predicates (the filtering `predicate`) remain available but unused by\ndefault_editor_menu.\n\nForward-only: Status.md + HANDOFF.md prepend a new top snapshot; plans/BASELINE.md\ninserts a new subsection ABOVE the W08-accelerator one; change.md appends a new\nentry. Historical snapshots/subsections preserved byte-identical.\n\nDocs only (4 files); no Rust source / test / Cargo change.\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only, no Rust touched).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
